></span>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class="icons inline-block">\r\n                    <span class="openstack block">&nbsp;</span>\r\n                    <span class="txt fix-font"></span>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class="icons inline-block">\r\n                    <span class="kvm block">&nbsp;</span>\r\n                    <span class="txt fix-font"></span>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class="icons inline-block">\r\n                    <span class="juniper block">&nbsp;</span>\r\n                    <span class="txt fix-font"></span>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class="gutterspace">&nbsp;</div>\r\n                <h3>Private Networking</h3>\r\n                <p>Setup your own network instantly in a few clicks.</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div id="support" class="tabcon donotshow">\r\n                <div class="illustration-base">&nbsp;</div>\r\n                <div class="bgimg">&nbsp;</div>\r\n                <h3>We are available 24/7 to help you with your queries</h3>\r\n                <p>Our servers include semi-managed support related to:</p>\r\n                <ul>\r\n                    <li class="fix-font">Boot, Login, Investigating Network/Hardware related issues</li>\r\n                    <li class="fix-font">Initial module installation and basic firewall setup</li>\r\n                    <li class="fix-font">Setup and re-installation of KVM VPS</li>\r\n                    <li class="fix-font">Core OS Updates &amp; Patches</li>\r\n                    <li class="fix-font">Reverse DNS Setup</li>\r\n                </ul>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="container" style="margin-top: 105px;">\r\n    <div class="row">\r\n        [whmpress_pricing_table_group id="4"]\r\n    </div>\r\n</div>\r\n[vc_row][vc_column][vc_tta_accordion c_align="center" active_section="1" title="FAQs"][vc_tta_section title="What are the advantages of VPS Hosting?" tab_id="1597251654731-0688c585-2da4"][vc_column_text]With VPS Hosting, you have complete isolation. This means that no matter what other users might be doing on the server, your VPS package will be unaffected. With root access, you can install whatever applications you require. VPS also gives you guaranteed resources, so no matter what, the CPU, RAM, Disk Space and Bandwidth allocated to your VPS package will always be available for your applications. It gives you all the features and functions of Dedicated server, without the additional cost.[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title="What is a KVM VPS?" tab_id="1597251654738-518c2a50-c843"][vc_column_text]A KVM (Kernel-based Virtual Machine) is a virtual private server which sits on top of a physical dedicated server. Resources are dedicated to the KVM VPS and are not shared with other users on the physical device, offering tremendous reliability and performance.[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title="What is the difference between KVM and OpenVZ?" tab_id="1597251740043-83eb363e-5ab2"][vc_column_text]A KVM is true virtualization where the VPS operates as its own server, independently of the host node. OpenVZ is a container based virtualization which relies on the host node\'s kernel[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title="What hosting panels are supported with HDD and SSD type plans ?" tab_id="1597251737522-d2324bb4-a0fa"][vc_column_text]When you buy any HDD server, we have an automated installation process configured, which installs cPanel on your package. For SSD servers, cPanel and Plesk are optional panels and can be purchased and installed.[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title="Is a Dedicated IP available?" tab_id="1597251816411-c11b015d-d01f"][vc_column_text]Yes, at an additional cost. You can raise a support ticket to get a dedicated IP.[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title="What kind of support do you offer?" tab_id="1597251850362-4273cba1-ba37"][vc_column_text]\r\n<div class="faq">\r\n    <div class="answer">Our support team will assist you in managing your servers. For a list of items that we support, please refer to the features mentioned above</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="faq"></div>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title="What is your backup policy?" tab_id="1597251877169-8436ce64-a87f"][vc_column_text]\r\n<div class="faq">\r\n    <div class="answer">You are responsible for your backups and web content. It is recommended that you keep copies of your content safe and make your own backups. You can take a backup from your cPanel or use a remote backup solution.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title="Is Upgrade/Downgrade possible?" tab_id="1597251908287-5516c77b-f4dc"][vc_column_text]\r\n<div class="faq">\r\n    <div class="answer">No, an upgrade or downgrade is not possible between the plans or resources.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title="Can I upgrade from HDD-based to SSD-based plan or vice-versa?" tab_id="1597251942399-4802252b-0a6a"][vc_column_text]\r\n<div class="faq us_plan_faq">\r\n    <div class="answer">Unfortunately, upgrades are not supported to plans having different storage type. You can only upgrade from a lower SSD plan to a higher SSD one and vice versa.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title="When should I choose SSD or HDD?" tab_id="1597251976281-84266cb8-e0ee"][vc_column_text]\r\n<div id="page-container" class="full-width-banner linux-kvm-page">\r\n    <div id="page-wrapper">\r\n        <div class="kvm-faq-wrapper">\r\n            <div class="kvm-faq-content">\r\n                <div class="faq us_plan_faq">\r\n                    <div class="answer last">SSD is recommended when you need high speed with limited disk space. HDD is suited for applications with more storage space and limited disk operati