<span>SSD &amp; SATA drives in RAID1</span></li>\r\n                    <li><span>Windows Server 2012, IIS 7.0</span></li>\r\n                </ul>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class="includes inline-block">\r\n                <h3>Program in Any Language </h3>\r\n                <ul>\r\n                    <li><span>Apache 2.2x</span></li>\r\n                    <li><span>ASP, ASP.NET 4.5, PHP 5.2 to 5.6</span></li>\r\n                    <li><span>Perl, CGI, Ruby On Rails</span></li>\r\n                    <li><span>MSSQL 2012, MySQL 5.5, MSAccess</span></li>\r\n                    <li><span>ASP JPEG, ASP Upload, JMail, SMTPMail</span></li>\r\n                    <li><span>Zend Optimizer, Zend Engine, ionCube Loader</span></li>\r\n                </ul>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class="includes inline-block">\r\n                <h3>Top-Notch Security</h3>\r\n                <ul>\r\n                    <li><span>Anti Spam &amp; Virus Protection</span></li>\r\n                    <li><span>Password Protect Directories</span></li>\r\n                    <li><span>Secure FTP Access</span></li>\r\n                    <li><span>IP Blocking</span></li>\r\n                    <li><span>phpMyAdmin Access</span></li>\r\n                    <li><span>Hotlink &amp; Leech Protection</span></li>\r\n                    <li><span>Cron Jobs for Scheduled Tasks</span></li>\r\n                    <li><span>Customizable Error Page</span></li>\r\n                    <li><span>Website Statistics with AWstats</span></li>\r\n                </ul>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n</div>\r\n[vc_row][vc_column][vc_tta_accordion active_section="1" title="FAQs"][vc_tta_section title="Q. What is Shared Web hosting?" tab_id="1597239331322-e68e460d-bb33"][vc_column_text]In Shared Web Hosting, multiple clients are hosted on a single server i.e. the clients share the server\'s resources. This helps reduce the cost, since the cost of the server and its resources are spread over all the clients/packages hosted on the server. Shared Hosting is perfect for personal websites, small and mid-sized businesses that do not require all the resources of a server.[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title="Q. Can I host multiple Web sites within one Shared Hosting plan?" tab_id="1597239331336-bd2cd26d-5388"][vc_column_text]Yes! Our Pro and Business shared hosting plans allow you to host more than one Website, by adding secondary domains through your hosting control panel i.e. cPanel.[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title="Q. Is there a Money Back Guarantee?" tab_id="1597239518010-6bac6fca-3659"][vc_column_text]Yes, we offer a 100% Risk Free, 30 day Money Back Guarantee.[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title="Q. Is Email hosting included in my package?" tab_id="1597239562564-0f6dac79-f331"][vc_column_text]Yes, all our Hosting packages come with Unlimited Email Hosting.[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title="Q. Can I upgrade to a higher plan?" tab_id="1597239630922-4c2aaf50-a434"][vc_column_text]Yes, you can easily upgrade to one of our higher plans at any time.[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title="Q. Is my data safe? Do you take backups?" tab_id="1597239696297-173ca8ad-d905"][vc_column_text]Yes, your data is a 100% secure and is backed-up every 5 days.[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title="Q. Do you include protection from viruses?" tab_id="1597239736379-3e5d1564-6b0a"][vc_column_text]Yes, all our servers are protected by Clam AV.[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title="Q. Can I divide my Shared Hosting package and resell it?" tab_id="1597239776210-61737821-aea9"][vc_column_text]While a Shared Hosting package cannot be used for this purpose, you can easily resell custom packages with our Reseller Hosting. To view our Reseller Hosting plans, \r\n<a href="https://websitesbymike.net/reseller-hosting.php">click\r\n    here.</a>[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title="Q. Do you offer SSH access?" tab_id="1597239808400-17650b5c-06fe"][vc_column_text]Yes, we provide SSH access to your domain. Because this is a shared environment, you will not get root access. However, you will be able to achieve most of your requirements by having the rights to access only the files relevant to your domain.[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title="Q. Who do I get in touch with if I need help?" tab_id="1597239842404-4f3de25a-74b9"][vc_column_text]Our Support team is always at hand to assist you. You can take a look at all our contact details \r\n<a href="https://websitesbymike.net/support/contact-us.php">here </a>.[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][/vc_tta_accordion][/vc_column][/vc_row]\r\n', 'Linux Shared Hosting', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1051-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-08-13 16:53:17', '2020-08-13 16:53:17', '', 1051, 'http://redcirclehost.local/1051-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1128, 2, '2020-08-13 16:56:29', '2020-08-13 16:56:29', '<div class="full-width-banner linux-kvm-page" >\r\n    <div class="vps-kvm-banner-wrapper">\r\n        <div class="vps-kvm-banner-content">\r\n            <h1 class="fix-font">Linux <span class="orange">KVM VPS Hosting</span></h1>\r\n            <div class="pagetitle fix-font">High-performance Servers for Faster<br>Websites &amp; Applications</div>\r\n            <ul>\r\n                <li class="fix-font">High-speed SSD Storage</li>\r\n                <li class="fix-font">Instant Provisioning</li>\r\n                <li class="fix-font">Full Root Access</li>\r\n            </ul>\r\n            <div class="starts-at">\r\n                <p class="fix-font">Starts at just\r\n                    <sup class="orange-text currency-symbol inline-block fix-font"> $</sup>\r\n                    <span class="orange-text starting-price inline-block fix-font">11.19<span class="orange-text time-period inline-block fix-font">/mo</span></span>\r\n                </p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div>\r\n                <a href="https://websitesbymike.net/virtualserverlinux-hosting.php#" class="kvm-link-2-plans inline-block fix-font">View Plans</a>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class="about-kvmvps-wrapper">\r\n        <div class="shadow">\r\n            <ul class="about-kvmvps-tabs">\r\n                <li class="choosentab"><a href="https://websitesbymike.net/virtualserverlinux-hosting.php#" title="deploy" class="fix-font">Deploy</a></li>\r\n                <li><a href="https://websitesbymike.net/virtualserverlinux-hosting.php#" title="manage" class="fix-font">Manage</a></li>\r\n                <li><a href="https://websitesbymike.net/virtualserverlinux-hosting.php#" title="secure" class="fix-font">Secure</a></li>\r\n                <li><a href="https://websitesbymike.net/virtualserverlinux-hosting.php#" title="support" class="fix-font">Get Support</a></li>\r\n            </ul>\r\n\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div class="about-kvmvps-content">\r\n            <div id="deploy" class="tabcon">\r\n                <div class="illustration-base">&nbsp;</div>\r\n                <div class="bgimg">&nbsp;</div>\r\n                <h3>Instant Provisioning</h3>\r\n                <p>Get up and running instantly! Our servers are provisioned within a<br>few minutes.</p>\r\n                <div class="gutterspace">&nbsp;</div>\r\n                <h3>Choose your Operating System</h3>\r\n                <p>Get complete flexibility to choose the operating system that works for you.<br>Here are operating systems available with our servers:</p>\r\n                <div class="icons inline-block">\r\n                    <span class="ubuntu block">&nbsp;</span>\r\n                    <span class="txt fix-font">Unbuntu</span>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class="icons inline-block">\r\n                    <span class="centos inline-block">&nbsp;</span>\r\n                    <span class="txt fix-font">Centos</span>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class="icons inline-block">\r\n                    <span class="debian block">&nbsp;</span>\r\n                    <span class="txt fix-font">Debian</span>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class="icons inline-block">\r\n                    <span class="fedora blockk">&nbsp;</span>\r\n                    <span class="txt fix-font">Fedora</span>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class="gutterspace">&nbsp;</div>\r\n                <h3>Choose your management panel</h3>\r\n                <p>Optionally, you can choose a Control Panel for easy Server Management.<br>Here the available add-ons:</p>\r\n                <div class="icons inline-block">\r\n                    <span class="cpanel block">&nbsp;</span>\r\n                    <span class="txt fix-font">cPanel/WHM</span>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class="icons inline-block">\r\n                    <span class="plesk block">&nbsp;</span>\r\n                    <span class="txt fix-font">Plesk</span>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class="icons inline-block">\r\n                    <span class="whmcs block">&nbsp;</span>\r\n                    <span class="txt fix-font">WHMCS</span>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div id="manage" class="tabcon donotshow">\r\n                <div class="manage-illustration">&nbsp;</div>\r\n                <h3>Server Management</h3>\r\n                <p>You can Start, Stop, Restart, Rebuild your VPS from the Server<br>Management Panel.</p>\r\n                <div class="gutterspace">&nbsp;</div>\r\n                <h3>Full Root Access</h3>\r\n                <p>With full root access, you get complete control to manage your server<br>resources.</p>\r\n                <div class="gutterspace">&nbsp;</div>\r\n                <h3>VNC Access</h3>\r\n                <p>VNC allows you quick access to your VPS for easy management.</p>\r\n                <div class="gutterspace">&nbsp;</div>\r\n                <h3>WHMCS</h3>\r\n                <p>Optionally, you can install &amp; integrate WHMCS with your VPS Server<br>seamlessly.</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div id="secure" class="tabcon donotshow">\r\n                <div class="illustration-base">&nbsp;</div>\r\n                <div class="bgimg">&nbsp;</div>\r\n                <h3>DDOS Protection</h3>\r\n                <p>Our advanced DDOS protection ensures that your VPS is protected<br>against any attacks.</p>\r\n                <div class="gutterspace">&nbsp;</div>\r\n                <h3>State-of-the-art Infrastructure</h3>\r\n                <p>All VPS servers are powered by trusted infrastructure to keep them up<br>and running:</p>\r\n                <div class="icons inline-block">\r\n                    <span class="nuestar block">&nbsp;</span>\r\n                    <span class="txt fix-font"></span>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class="icons inline-block">\r\n                    <span class="openstack block">&nbsp;</span>\r\n                    <span class="txt fix-font"></span>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class="icons inline-block">\r\n                    <span class="kvm block">&nbsp;</span>\r\n                    <span class="txt fix-font"></span>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class="icons inline-block">\r\n                    <span class="juniper block">&nbsp;</span>\r\n                    <span class="txt fix-font"></span>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class="gutterspace">&nbsp;</div>\r\n                <h3>Private Networking</h3>\r\n                <p>Setup your own network instantly in a few clicks.</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div id="support" class="tabcon donotshow">\r\n                <div class="illustration-base">&nbsp;</div>\r\n                <div class="bgimg">&nbsp;</div>\r\n                <h3>We are available 24/7 to help you with your queries</h3>\r\n                <p>Our servers include semi-managed support related to:</p>\r\n                <ul>\r\n                    <li class="fix-font">Boot, Login, Investigating Network/Hardware related issues</li>\r\n                    <li class="fix-font">Initial module installation and basic firewall setup</li>\r\n                    <li class="fix-font">Setup and re-installation of KVM VPS</li>\r\n                    <li class="fix-font">Core OS Updates &amp; Patches</li>\r\n                    <li class="fix-font">Reverse DNS Setup</li>\r\n                </ul>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="container" style="margin-top: 105px;">\r\n    <div class="row">\r\n        [whmpress_pricing_table_group id="4"]\r\n    </div>\r\n</div>\r\n[vc_row][vc_column][vc_tta_accordion c_align="center" active_section="1" title="FAQs"][vc_tta_section title="What are the advantages of VPS Hosting?" tab_id="1597251654731-0688c585-2da4"][vc_column_text]With VPS Hosting, you have complete isolation. This means that no matter what other users might be doing on the server, your VPS package will be unaffected. With root access, you can install whatever applications you require. VPS also gives you guaranteed resources, so no matter what, the CPU, RAM, Disk Space and Bandwidth allocated to your VPS package will always be available for your applications. It gives you all the features and functions of Dedicated server, without the additional cost.[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title="What is a KVM VPS?" tab_id="1597251654738-518c2a50-c843"][vc_column_text]A KVM (Kernel-based Virtual Machine) is a virtual private server which sits on top of a physical dedicated server. Resources are dedicated to the KVM VPS and are not shared with other users on the physical device, offering tremendous reliability and performance.[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title="What is the difference between KVM and OpenVZ?" tab_id="1597251740043-83eb363e-5ab2"][vc_column_text]A KVM is true virtualization where the VPS operates as its own server, independently of the host node. OpenVZ is a container based virtualization which relies on the host node\'s kernel[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title="What hosting panels are supported with HDD and SSD type plans ?" tab_id="1597251737522-d2324bb4-a0fa"][vc_column_text]When you buy any HDD server, we have an automated installation process configured, which installs cPanel on your package. For SSD servers, cPanel and Plesk are optional panels and can be purchased and installed.[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title="Is a Dedicated IP available?" tab_id="1597251816411-c11b015d-d01f"][vc_column_text]Yes, at an additional cost. You can raise a support ticket to get a dedicated IP.[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title="What kind of support do you offer?" tab_id="1597251850362-4273cba1-ba37"][vc_column_text]\r\n<div class="faq">\r\n    <div class="answer">Our support team will assist you in managing your servers. For a list of items that we support, please refer to the features mentioned above</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="faq"></div>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title="What is your backup policy?" tab_id="1597251877169-8436ce64-a87f"][vc_column_text]\r\n<div class="faq">\r\n    <div class="answer">You are responsible for your backups and web content. It is recommended that you keep copies of your content safe and make your own backups. You can take a backup from your cPanel or use a remote backup solution.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title="Is Upgrade/Downgrade possible?" tab_id="1597251908287-5516c77b-f4dc"][vc_column_text]\r\n<div class="faq">\r\n    <div class="answer">No, an upgrade or downgrade is not possible between the plans or resources.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title="Can I upgrade from HDD-based to SSD-based plan or vice-versa?" tab_id="1597251942399-4802252b-0a6a"][vc_column_text]\r\n<div class="faq us_plan_faq">\r\n    <div class="answer">Unfortunately, upgrades are not supported to plans having different storage type. You can only upgrade from a lower SSD plan to a higher SSD one and vice versa.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title="When should I choose SSD or HDD?" tab_id="1597251976281-84266cb8-e0ee"][vc_column_text]\r\n<div id="page-container" class="full-width-banner linux-kvm-page">\r\n    <div id="page-wrapper">\r\n        <div class="kvm-faq-wrapper">\r\n            <div class="kvm-faq-content">\r\n                <div class="faq us_plan_faq">\r\n                    <div class="answer last">SSD is recommended when you need high speed with limited disk space. HDD is suited for applications with more storage space and limited disk operations.</div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n</div>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][/vc_tta_accordion][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Linux KVM VPS', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1120-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-08-13 16:56:29', '2020-08-13 16:56:29', '', 1120, 'http://redcirclehost.local/1120-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
